Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the noodles.

Trim the @green beans{150%grams}, then chop into thirds.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @ginger{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{to taste} in a large #pan{} on medium-high heat.

When hot, add the @Irish beef mince{250%grams} and fry until browned, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

When cooked, transfer the mince to a #medium bowl{} and mix in the @teriyaki sauce{2%sachets}. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the water is boiling, stir in the @udon noodles{300%grams}.

Bring back to the boil, then cook, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once done, drain in a #sieve{}.

> TIP: Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Return the (now empty) pan to medium heat.

Once hot, add the pepper, green beans and a small splash of @water{to taste} to help them cook.

Stir-fry until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the ginger and garlic, cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the beef mince back into the pan and stir in the noodles.

Toss to coat and continue to cook until everything is combined and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once hot, remove the pan from the heat and season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Divide the beef noodles between your bowls.